<Base
  title="About"
  description="Hassan Mamdani — background, career, and what this site is about."
>
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>About</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      I'm Hassan Mamdani. I live in Cambridge, UK.
    </p>

    <p>
      My career has moved around more than most. I started in preclinical drug discovery —
      bench science, then project and programme management. From there I moved into IT systems
      implementation: LIMS, ELN, ERP, compound management. Then into operations and leadership.
      I'm currently COO and CFO of <a href="https://www.openingworlds.co.uk">Opening Worlds Ltd</a>,
      a small company that makes KS2 humanities curriculum for primary schools.
    </p>

    <p>
      The common thread, if there is one, is that I tend to end up in roles where the job is
      to make complicated things work — across teams, systems, organisations. Not because I'm
      the deepest expert in any one domain, but because I can hold enough of several domains
      in my head at once to see where they connect and where they don't.
    </p>

    <p>
      I've spent a long time treating that as a weakness. I'm writing through whether that's right.
    </p>

    <h2>This site</h2>

    <p>
      I write here about being a generalist — the experience of breadth without obvious depth,
      and what it's actually like to build a career that way. No particular angle or agenda.
      Just things I'm thinking through.
    </p>

    <p>
      I don't publish often. When I do, it's because I have something worth saying,
      not to fill a schedule.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>

    <p>
      The best way to reach me is on <a href="https://twitter.com/hassantm">X / Twitter</a>,
      or by email at <a href="mailto:h@htmweb.com">h@htmweb.com</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
